 surface density $\\Sigma$ of GMCs is not approximately constant\nas previously believed, but varies by $\\sim 3$ orders of magnitude. We also\nshow that the size and velocity dispersion of GMC population across galaxies\nare related to the surface density, as expected from the gravitational and\npressure equilibrium, i.e. $\\sigma_v R^{-1/2} \\propto \\Sigma^{1/2}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Feb 2015 21:00:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-04-13"}
